ObservableGame - Class in it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers
This class is the class that represent the Observer pattern used in Distributed MVC pattern used to create Santorini's video game, it is a class that represent a game that can be observer from ObserverRemoteView to gain information about the change of the game state using Observer pattern.
ObservableGame() - Constructor for class it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers.ObservableGame
Creates and observable game with a list of ObserverRemoteView ready to be changed.
ObservableObject - Class in it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers
This class represents a general observable object from an arbitrary number of observers of the type of ObserverObject.
ObservableObject() - Constructor for class it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers.ObservableObject
This constructor creates an observable object with an empty list of observers ready to be changed.
ObservableRemoteView - Class in it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers
This class represent the Observer for remote views inside the Distributed MVC pattern used to design Santorini video game, this class represent a remote view which communicate with a ObserverController to update the server about the choices done by the player during a match.
ObservableRemoteView() - Constructor for class it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers.ObservableRemoteView
Creates an observable remote view that can be observed by one ObserverController.

observerQuit(ObservableRemoteView) - Method in class it.polimi.ingsw.controller.ServerController
This method is called when a player which is only observing the match wants to quit the game, it make it quit and changes the model, if the player isn't inside the game as observer an AssertionError is thrown because there has been an error on handling the observers.
observerQuit(ObservableRemoteView) - Method in interface it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers.ObserverController
Updates the observer when the observer calls this method because a player has quit.
ObserverRemoteView - Interface in it.polimi.ingsw.util.observers
This is the class that represent the Observer pattern for remote view inside the Distributed MVC pattern, this object will be overridden by the remote view of the server that implements the Distributed MVC remote view pattern.
